'''Even Lange''' (born 5 June 1946) is a Norwegian [[economic history|economic historian]].
He was born in [[Oslo]] as the son of politician [[Halvard Manthey Lange]] (1902–1970) and teacher Aase Monsen (1911–1979). On the maternal side he was a nephew of [[Randi Monsen|Randi]] and [[Per Monsen]], and on the paternal side he was a nephew of [[August Lange]],<ref name=nbl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=|title=Even Lange|encyclopedia=[[Norsk biografisk leksikon]]|first=Knut|last=Sogner|volume=|editor=[[Knut Helle|Helle, Knut]]|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/.nbl_biografi/Even_Lange/utdypning|language=Norwegian|accessdate=16 April 2009}}</ref> [[Carl Viggo Manthey Lange]] and a grandson of [[Christian Lous Lange]].<ref>{{cite encyclopedia|year=2007|url=http://www.snl.no/Lange/slekt_fra_Holstein|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=Henriksen, Petter|first=Terje|last=Bratberg|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|title=Lange – slekt fra Holstein|language=Norwegian|accessdate=16 April 2009}}</ref> He has married twice.<ref name=nbl/>
Influenced by [[Joseph Schumpeter]], his field is [[economic history]].<ref name=nbl/> He worked at the [[National Archival Services of Norway]] from 1979 to 1988,<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia|year=2007|url=http://www.snl.no/Even_Lange|encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=Henriksen, Petter|first=Tor Ragnar|last=Weidling|publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget|location=Oslo|title=Even Lange|language=Norwegian|accessdate=16 April 2009}}</ref> and from 1988 to 2000 he led the Centre for Business History at the [[BI Norwegian Business School]].<ref name=nbl/> He worked at the [[Norwegian Institute for Social Research]] for two years before being appointed as a professor at the [[University of Oslo]] in 2002.<ref name=snl/> From 1995 to 2002 he was a member of the Council of the [[European Business History Association (EBHA)|European Business History Association]]. His first major work was ''Treforedlingens epoke 1895–1970'', volume four of the work ''Fra Linderud til Eidsvold Værk'', which was released in 1985 and earned him the doctorate in 1987. In 1997 he published ''Samling om felles mål 1935–1970'', volume eleven of ''Aschehougs Norgeshistorie'' on general Norwegian history.<ref name=nbl/> He is a member of the [[Norwegian Academy of Science and Letters]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dnva.no/c26848/artikkel/vis.html?tid=27637|title=Gruppe 1: Historie|publisher=[[Norwegian Academy of Science and Letters]]|language=Norwegian|accessdate=26 October 2009}}</ref>
