{{Infobox member of the Knesset |image = |birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1933|2|14|df=y}} |birth_place = [[Magdiel]], [[Mandatory Palestine]] |death_date = |death_place = |Knesset(s) = [[Israeli legislative election, 1988|12]], [[Israeli legislative election, 1992|13]] |party1 = [[Alignment (political party)|Alignment]] |partyyears1 = 1988–1991 |party2 = [[Israeli Labor Party|Labor Party]] |partyyears2 = 1991–1996 }}
'''Gedalia Gal''' ({{lang-he|גדליה גל}}, born 14 February 1933) is an [[Israel]]i farmer and former politician who served as a member of the [[Knesset]] for the [[Alignment (political party)|Alignment]] and [[Israeli Labor Party|Labor Party]] from 1988 until 1996.
==Biography== Born in [[Magdiel]] during the [[Mandatory Palestine|Mandate era]], Gal attended a professional high school and went on to work in agriculture, including emissary work for the [[Moshavim Movement]].<ref>[https://www.knesset.gov.il/mk/eng/mk_eng.asp?mk_individual_id_t=142 Gedalya Gal: Public Activities] Knesset website</ref>
In [[Israeli legislative election, 1988|1988]] he was elected to the Knesset on the Alignment list. In 1992 he was heavily involved in what became known as the "Gal law", which dealt with moshavim's debts. He was re-elected in [[Israeli legislative election, 1992|1992]], by which time the Alignment had been disscolved and merged into the Labor Party. During his second term he chaired the influential Finance Committee and was involved in the 1996 Electricity Law. He was involved in the [[Third Way (Israel)|Third Way]] movement, but did not join when it became an official party, preferring to remain in the Labor Party. However, he lost his seat in the [[Israeli legislative election, 1996|1996 elections]].
After leaving the Knesset he was appointed CEO of [[Tnuva]] dairy company, a post he held until 2001. He later chaired the board of the [[Society for the Protection of Nature in Israel]] and the [[Battle of Ammunition Hill|Ammunition Hill]] museum. Today he lived in [[Kfar Vitkin]] and is involved in livestock rearing.<ref>[http://www.mnh.tau.ac.il/upload/Gedalia_Gal.pdf Gedalia Gal] Tel Aviv University</ref>
