ichner]] R |- |Nebraska | [[Jim Smith (Nebraska politician)|Jim Smith]] R |- |Nevada | [[Barbara Cegavske]] R |- |rowspan=2|New Hampshire | [[Gary Daniels|Gary L. Daniels]] R |- | [[Jordan G. Ulery]] R |- |rowspan=2|New Jersey | [[Steve Oroho]] R |- | [[Jay Webber]] R |- |rowspan=2|New Mexico | [[Paul C. Bandy]] R |- | [[William Payne (New Mexico politician)|William Payne]] R |- |New York | [[Owen H. Johnson]] R |- |North Carolina | [[Fred F. Steen, II|Fred F. Steen II]] R |- |rowspan=2|North Dakota | [[Alan H. Carlson]] R |- | [[Bette Grande]] R |- |Ohio | [[John Adams (Ohio politician)|John Adams]] R |} | {| class="wikitable" |- ! State ! Leaders (Party) |- |rowspan=2|Oklahoma | [[Gary Banz]] R |- | [[Cliff Aldridge]] R |- |Oregon | [[Gene Whisnant]] R |- |Pennsylvania | [[Brian L. Ellis]] R |- |rowspan=2|Rhode Island | [[Francis T. Maher Jr.]] R |- | [[Jon D. Brien]] D |- |rowspan=2|South Carolina | [[Liston Barfield]] R |- | [[Thomas C. Alexander (politician)|Thomas Alexander]] R |- |rowspan=2|South Dakota | [[Deb Peters]] R |- | [[Val Rausch|Valentine B. Rausch]] R |- |Tennessee | [[Curry Todd]] R |- |rowspan=3|Texas | [[Charles F. Howard]] R |- | [[Jim Jackson (Texas politician)|Jim Jackson]] R |- | [[Kel Seliger]] R |- |rowspan=3|Utah | [[Curtis S. Bramble]] R |- | [[Wayne L. Niederhauser]] R |- | [[Christopher Herrod|Chris Herrod]] R |- |Vermont | [[Kevin J. Mullin]] R |- |rowspan=2|Virginia | [[John Cosgrove (Virginia politician)|John A. Cosgrove Jr.]] R |- | [[Stephen H. Martin]] R |- |rowspan=2|Washington | [[Jan Angel]] R |- | [[Don Benton]] R |- |West Virginia | [[Eric Householder]] R |- |rowspan=2|Wisconsin | |- | [[Robin J. Vos]] R |- |Wyoming | [[Pete Illoway|Peter S. Illoway]] R |} |}
==Task force members==
ALEC presently has 9 task forces to "commission research, publish papers, convene workshops, issue alerts, and serve as clearinghouses of information on free market policies in the states." Each task force is co-chaired by one state legislator (termed "public") and one corporate representative(termed "private"), but Private Co-Chairs have veto power over final decisions of their task force. The primary goal of these task forces is to develop model policies for the country. "The centerpiece to the Task Forces is ALEC's model legislation. To date, ALEC has considered, written, and approved hundreds of model bills, resolutions, and policy statements."<ref name="Task Forces">{{cite web |url=http://www.alec.org/task-forces/ |title=Task Forces; &#124; ALEC – American Legislative Exchange Council |publisher=Alec.org, copyright 2013 |accessdate=August 17, 2013 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130902101217/http://www.alec.org/task-forces/ |archivedate=September 2, 2013 |df=mdy-all }}</ref>
